{"title": "End of streaming: Worries over mixing with Normal students may drive parents to chase IP schools", "tags": "singapore", "timestamp": "2019-03-10", "content": "Most Singaporeans have cheered the latest move to scrap streaming and improve social mixing in secondary schools, but some have voiced concerns that a seemingly privileged group of schools have been left out of the picture.\nThe Integrated Programme (IP) schools, which allow students to skip the O levels and go straight to their A levels or International Baccalaureate, along with schools which take in only Express stream students, will be largely untouched by the changes."}